Definition: a political movement uniting Palestinian Arabs in an effort to create an independent state of Palestine
Example: when formed in 1964 it was a terrorist organization dominated by Yasser Arafat's al-Fatah; in 1968 Arafat became chairman; received recognition by the United Nations and by Arab states in 1974 as a government in exile; has played a largely political role since the creation of the Palestine National Authority
Synonyms: PLO, political_movement, noun, location, Palestine, r, a, political, movement, uniting, Palestinian, Arabs, in, an, effort, to, create, independent, state, of, when, formed, it, was, terrorist, organization, dominated, by, Yasser, Arafat, s, al-Fatah, became, chairman, received, recognition, the, United, Nations, and, Arab, states, as, government, exile, has, played, largely, role, since, creation, National, Authority
Category: noun.group
